      "\nSo, let's complete the proof of lemma2.\n\n```tactics\nimport Mathlib.Tactic.NormNum\nimport Mathlib.Tactic.IntervalCases\n\nimport ProblemExtraction\n\nproblem_file { tags := [.Combinatorics] }\n\n/-!\n# Bulgarian Mathematical Olympiad 1998, Problem 1\n\nWe will be considering colorings in 2 colors of n (distinct) points\nAРѓЂ, AРѓѓ, ..., AРѓЎ. Call such a coloring \"good\" if there exist three points\nAрхб, AР▒╝, AРѓѓР▒╝РѓІрхб, 1 РЅц i < 2j - i РЅц n, which are colored the same color.\n\nFind the least natural number n (n РЅЦ 3) such that all colorings\nof n points are good.\n-/\n\nnamespace Bulgaria1998P1\n\nabbrev coloring_is_good {m : РёЋ} (color : Set.Icc 1 m Рєњ Fin 2) : Prop :=\n  РѕЃ i j : Set.Icc 1 m,\n    i < j РѕД\n    РѕЃ h3 : 2 * j.val - i Рѕѕ Set.Icc 1 m,\n    color i = color j РѕД color i = color РЪе2 * j - i, h3РЪЕ\n\nabbrev all_colorings_are_good (m : РёЋ) : Prop :=\n  3 РЅц m РѕД Рѕђ color : Set.Icc 1 m Рєњ Fin 2, coloring_is_good color\n\nsnip begin\n\nlemma lemma1 {m n : РёЋ} (hmn : m РЅц n) (hm : all_colorings_are_good m) :\n    all_colorings_are_good n := by\n  constructor\n  ┬и exact hm.1.trans hmn\n  ┬и intro c\n    let c' : Set.Icc 1 m Рєњ Fin 2 :=\n      fun x Рєд c РЪеx.val, by rw [Set.mem_Icc]; exact РЪеx.prop.1, x.prop.2.trans hmnРЪЕРЪЕ\n    obtain РЪеРЪеi, hi1, hi2РЪЕ, РЪеj, hj1, hj2РЪЕ, hij1, hij2, hc1, hc2РЪЕ := hm.2 c'\n    use РЪеi, hi1, hi2.trans hmnРЪЕ\n    use РЪеj, hj1, hj2.trans hmnРЪЕ\n    simp only [Subtype.mk_lt_mk, Set.mem_Icc, tsub_le_iff_right, exists_and_left]\n    simp only [Subtype.mk_lt_mk] at hij1\n    refine РЪеhij1, ?_РЪЕ\n    simp only [Set.mem_Icc, tsub_le_iff_right] at hij2\n    simp only [c'] at hc1\n    refine РЪеhc1, ?_РЪЕ\n    have hij2' : 1 РЅц 2 * j - i РѕД 2 * j РЅц n + i :=\n       РЪеhij2.1, le_add_of_le_add_right hij2.2 hmnРЪЕ\n    use hij2'\n\ndef coloring_of_eight {n : РёЋ} : Set.Icc 1 n Рєњ Fin 2\n| РЪе1, _РЪЕ => 0\n| РЪе2, _РЪЕ => 1\n| РЪе3, _РЪЕ => 0\n| РЪе4, _РЪЕ => 1\n| РЪе5, _РЪЕ => 1\n| РЪе6, _РЪЕ => 0\n| РЪе7, _РЪЕ => 1\n| РЪе8, _РЪЕ => 0\n| _ => 0 -- unreachable\n\nlemma lemma2 :\n    РѕЃ f : Set.Icc 1 8 Рєњ Fin 2, ┬гcoloring_is_good f := by\n  use coloring_of_eight\n  intro h\n  obtain РЪеРЪеi, hi1, hi2РЪЕ, РЪеj, hj1, hj2РЪЕ, hij1, hij2, hc1, hc2РЪЕ := h\n  dsimp [coloring_of_eight] at *\n  interval_cases i <;> interval_cases j <;> sorry --aesop (simp_config := {decide := true})\n```\n\nSo, we need to complete the proof of lemma2. The proof strategy is to show that for n = 8, the specific coloring defined by `coloring_of_eight` is not good. To do this, we assume that it is good (i.e., there exists a monochromatic triple) and derive a contradiction.\n\nSo, after `intro h` and `obtain ... := h`, we have:\n- `i, j` are points in `Set.Icc 1 8` such that `i < j`\n- `2 * j.val - i` is also in `Set.Icc 1 8`\n- `hc1: color i = color j`\n- `hc2: color i = color (2 * j - i)`\n\nSo, we need to compute `hc1` and `hc2` with the specific `coloring_of_eight` and derive a contradiction.\n\nSo, let's compute `hc1` and `hc2`.\n\nWe have `i` and `j` in `Set.Icc 1 8`, so `1 РЅц i РЅц 8` and `1 РЅц j РЅц 8`, and `i < j`.\n\nAlso, `1 РЅц 2 * j.val - i РЅц 8`.\n\nSo, `hc1` says that `color i = color j`.\n`hc2` says that `color i = color (2 * j - i)`.\n\nSo, `color i = color j = color (2 * j - i)`. So, all three have the same color.\n\nBut with the specific definition of `coloring_of_eight`, this leads to a contradiction.\n\nSo, we need to compute the color of i, j, and 2j-i and show that they can't all be the same.\n\nSo, let's compute.\n\nWe have `i` and `j` from 1 to 8, with `i < j`, and `1 РЅц 2j - i РЅц 8`.\n\nSo, `2j - i РЅц 8` means `2j РЅц 8 + i`, which is true since `j РЅц 8`.\n\nSo, `1 РЅц 2j - i`. So, `i РЅц 2j - 1`.\n\nSo, `i < j` and `i РЅц 2j - 1`. So, `i` is from 1 to 8, `j` is from `i+1` to 8, and `2j - i РЅЦ 1`.\n\nSo, for each possible pair (i, j), we need to compute the color of i, j, and 2j-i and show that they can't all be the same.\n\nSo, let'