The proof of lemma2 shows that for n = 8, all colorings are good. The proof uses the pigeonhole principle. For any coloring of 8 points, there must be four points of the same color. In any set of four points, there must be a good triple.

The proof of lemma2 uses interval_cases to check all possible pairs of i and j. For each pair, it checks that the coloring must have a good triple.

